# Node version (nvm)

This project pins Node in [`.nvmrc`](.nvmrc) and `package.json` `engines` (currently **24.15.0**).

Before running any Node/npm command in the terminal (`npm`, `npx`, `node`, `turbo`, etc.):

1. From the repo root, run `nvm use` (or ensure the active shell already used it this session).
2. Prefer chaining in one command: `nvm use && npm run build`
3. If `nvm use` fails because the version is not installed, run `nvm install` first, then retry.

Do not assume the system default Node version is correct — verify with `node -v` after `nvm use` when troubleshooting engine or Vite errors.
